                    "creatorType": "author",
                    "firstName": "Kazimieras",
                    "lastName": "Baranauskas"
                }
            ],
            "abstractNote": "Abstract. Bat hibernation conditions as well as diversity and abundance of hibernating bats were investigated in the Paneriai tunnel (Vilnius, Lithuania) in 20002003. Five bat species were found to hibernate in the tunnel: Daubentons bat (Myotis daubentonii), pond bat (Myotis dasycneme), brown long-eared bat (Plecotus auritus), barbastelle bat (Barbastella barbastellus), and serotine bat (Eptesicus serotinus). It was established that about 130 bats roost in the hibernation site every year, Daubentons bats constituting 72% of them. That is the largest known hibernating cluster of Daubentons bats in southeastern Lithuania. The Paneriai tunnel is protected as an engineering monument. It is recommended that the tunnel should be granted the status of a bat reserve.",
